# PowerShell curl JSON Rule

When running `curl.exe` in PowerShell with `Content-Type: application/json`, avoid inline JSON strings in command arguments.

Use a JSON file payload instead:

```powershell
'{"key":"value"}' | Set-Content -NoNewline -Encoding utf8 request.json
curl.exe -i -X POST "http://localhost:8080/path" -H "Content-Type: application/json" --data-binary "@request.json"
```

Rationale:
- PowerShell quoting/escaping can corrupt inline JSON.
- File payload avoids quote parsing issues and makes requests reproducible.

If a user asks for curl examples on Windows/PowerShell, prefer `--data-binary "@request.json"` format by default.
